com.tsgrp.migration.event

Class RepeatingAttrValueSelectorListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tsgrp.migration.event.AbstractListener
      • com.tsgrp.migration.event.RepeatingAttrValueSelectorListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener

    public class RepeatingAttrValueSelectorListener
extends AbstractListener
implements TargetBeginImportNodeEventListener
    Problem- We want to use the last value of a repeating attribute to migrate to a single attribute. Solution- PullNthItemFromRepeater This listener will find the nth item of a repeating attribute and assign the value to the injected target attribute. If the injected position value ('n') is negative, the the listener will count backwards from the end of the list. For example, consider a list like the following: {6,7,8,9}. Position=0 would return the value 6. Position=3 would return the value 9. Position=-1 would return the value 9. Position=-2 would return the value 8. If the injected position is out of bounds, the listener will use the fallbackPosition (if specified).
    Since:
    Oct 25, 2011
